<title>USA: USAir says to pay $50 mln to preferred arrears.</title>
<headline>USAir says to pay $50 mln to preferred arrears.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-01-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>USAir Group Inc said that in 1997 it will make a special payment of $50 million toward preferred dividend arrears to senior preferred stockholders</p>
<p>In 1996, USAir said it recorded preferred dividends of $88.8 million.</p>
<p>The company is not currently paying regular preferred stock dividends, it said.</p>
<p>Financial accounting principles require that the regular preferred dividends, however, be reflected in the company's statements of operations, the company said.</p>
